SIMPLE: unipersonal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unipersonal
<hw>U"ni*per"son*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Uni-</ets> + <ets>personal</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Existing as one, and only one, person; <as>as, a
<ex>unipersonal</ex> God</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>Used in only one person,
especially only in the third person, as some verbs;
impersonal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unipersonalist</ent>⟦br⟧
